<h2>Textbooks<a name="Textbooks"></a></h2>
<p>The official textbook for this course is</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Computer Networking: A Top-Down Approach</b>, 7th edition, by
James F. Kurose and Keith W. Ross.</li>
</ul>

As further background, we suggest

<ul>

<li><b>Computer Networks: A Systems Approach</b>, 5th
edition, by Larry Peterson and Bruce Davie.</li>

<li><b>Computer Networking: Principles, protocols, and practice</b> by
Olivier Bonaventure. The <a
href="https://www.computer-networking.info/">third edition</a> of this
textbook is <a
href="https://github.com/cnp3/ebook/releases/download/draft-3rd/CNP3-2021.pdf">openly
and freely available.</a>

